WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.824 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:01.824 --> 00:00:06.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Our world today seems
to be in total upheaval.

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.140 align:middle line:84%
Many people are wondering
if, in fact, we have not

00:00:08.140 --> 00:00:09.590 align:middle line:90%
reached the biblical end times.

00:00:09.590 --> 00:00:12.995 align:middle line:90%


00:00:12.995 --> 00:00:15.120 align:middle line:90%
But how can we know?

00:00:15.120 --> 00:00:18.030 align:middle line:84%
Are we simply to be
spectators to these events?

00:00:18.030 --> 00:00:20.310 align:middle line:84%
Or have we been
given information--

00:00:20.310 --> 00:00:25.620 align:middle line:84%
messages that offer hope or
even help avoid these disasters?

00:00:25.620 --> 00:00:29.940 align:middle line:84%
In 2004, a particle physicist
working independently

00:00:29.940 --> 00:00:32.310 align:middle line:84%
made a discovery
that could change

00:00:32.310 --> 00:00:35.970 align:middle line:84%
everything we think we know
about the world we live in.

00:00:35.970 --> 00:00:38.640 align:middle line:84%
Could it be that something
as inconsequential

00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:44.800 align:middle line:84%
as this tiny fiber contains such
a message for the entire world?

00:00:44.800 --> 00:00:47.880 align:middle line:84%
Have new ways of obtaining
long hidden information

00:00:47.880 --> 00:00:49.620 align:middle line:90%
been discovered?

00:00:49.620 --> 00:00:53.160 align:middle line:10%
>> The emissions from a
physical object or when studied

00:00:53.160 --> 00:00:57.210 align:middle line:10%
as a whole uniquely identify
events in the history of that

00:00:57.210 --> 00:00:58.110 align:middle line:10%
object.

00:00:58.110 --> 00:01:00.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Have scientists finally
discovered where to look

00:01:00.990 --> 00:01:03.820 align:middle line:90%
for the secrets of the universe?

00:01:03.820 --> 00:01:06.630 align:middle line:10%
>> And we have a piece of cloth.

00:01:06.630 --> 00:01:12.950 align:middle line:10%
And it leads us to a mysterious
gate, which opens for us.

00:01:12.950 --> 00:01:17.100 align:middle line:10%
And it lets us to see a
completely different world,

00:01:17.100 --> 00:01:22.140 align:middle line:10%
an extraordinary world
with extraordinary laws.

00:01:22.140 --> 00:01:25.290 align:middle line:84%
>> What is this
mysterious gateway?

00:01:25.290 --> 00:01:27.420 align:middle line:84%
And what are these
extraordinary laws that

00:01:27.420 --> 00:01:29.820 align:middle line:90%
are only now being discovered?

00:01:29.820 --> 00:01:34.140 align:middle line:84%
Could it be that time, space,
and energy interact in a way

00:01:34.140 --> 00:01:36.630 align:middle line:90%
never before predicted?

00:01:36.630 --> 00:01:40.650 align:middle line:84%
>> Physicists are always trying
to find unifying principles.

00:01:40.650 --> 00:01:44.010 align:middle line:84%
Is there a unifying principle of
the very, very large relativity

00:01:44.010 --> 00:01:46.380 align:middle line:84%
and the very, very small
quantum physics, which

00:01:46.380 --> 00:01:48.840 align:middle line:84%
if we could see what
that principle was,

00:01:48.840 --> 00:01:51.840 align:middle line:90%
we could explain everything?

00:01:51.840 --> 00:01:54.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Has that principle
been discovered?

00:01:54.180 --> 00:01:56.550 align:middle line:84%
Is modern science now
beginning to decode

00:01:56.550 --> 00:02:00.690 align:middle line:84%
messages that might even be
coming from another dimension?

00:02:00.690 --> 00:02:03.270 align:middle line:10%
Is there something on the
scientific horizon that

00:02:03.270 --> 00:02:06.420 align:middle line:10%
suggests we have finally been
given the secrets of life

00:02:06.420 --> 00:02:07.350 align:middle line:10%
itself--

00:02:07.350 --> 00:02:10.715 align:middle line:10%
perhaps even eternal life?

00:02:10.715 --> 00:02:12.590 align:middle line:84%
>> There's something
which produces the order

00:02:12.590 --> 00:02:13.390 align:middle line:90%
of the universe.

00:02:13.390 --> 00:02:16.070 align:middle line:84%
Now the big problem
is we don't quite

00:02:16.070 --> 00:02:18.360 align:middle line:90%
know what that something is.

00:02:18.360 --> 00:02:22.280 align:middle line:84%
So even though I talk like
we do, believe me, folks.

00:02:22.280 --> 00:02:27.570 align:middle line:84%
There's a big mystery still out
there waiting to be discovered.

00:02:27.570 --> 00:02:31.070 align:middle line:84%
>> The nature of time, the
creation of the universe,

00:02:31.070 --> 00:02:34.040 align:middle line:84%
and perhaps even a link
to another dimension--

00:02:34.040 --> 00:02:36.980 align:middle line:84%
can these great riddles of
the universe be solved through

00:02:36.980 --> 00:02:39.710 align:middle line:90%
the lens of the ancient past?

00:02:39.710 --> 00:02:41.990 align:middle line:84%
In the next hour, you will
stand at the threshold

00:02:41.990 --> 00:02:44.930 align:middle line:84%
of today's most stunning
scientific discoveries.

00:02:44.930 --> 00:02:47.090 align:middle line:84%
Images never before
seen will reach out

00:02:47.090 --> 00:02:50.540 align:middle line:84%
from the dust of antiquity and
touch your life today in ways

00:02:50.540 --> 00:02:52.370 align:middle line:90%
you never thought possible.

00:02:52.370 --> 00:02:55.580 align:middle line:84%
In a moment, scholars,
scientists, and historians

00:02:55.580 --> 00:02:59.000 align:middle line:84%
all come together in an amazing
and unflinching investigation

00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:01.370 align:middle line:90%
into the fabric of time.

00:03:01.370 --> 00:03:06.080 align:middle line:90%


00:03:06.080 --> 00:03:07.520 align:middle line:10%
In a world where
children grow up

00:03:07.520 --> 00:03:10.040 align:middle line:10%
playing with computers
and calculus is frequently

00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:12.260 align:middle line:10%
part of the high
school curriculum,

00:03:12.260 --> 00:03:14.570 align:middle line:10%
many of the scientific
mysteries of the past

00:03:14.570 --> 00:03:17.060 align:middle line:10%
are today commonplace knowledge.

00:03:17.060 --> 00:03:19.100 align:middle line:84%
Yet, even the world's
leading scientists

00:03:19.100 --> 00:03:21.860 align:middle line:84%
would agree that when it comes
to understanding the universe

00:03:21.860 --> 00:03:25.400 align:middle line:84%
we live in and the physical
laws that we think govern it,

00:03:25.400 --> 00:03:28.850 align:middle line:84%
only a very few of the threads
that make up this vast tapestry

00:03:28.850 --> 00:03:30.830 align:middle line:90%
have been untangled.

00:03:30.830 --> 00:03:34.700 align:middle line:84%
But these few threads
are endlessly intriguing.

00:03:34.700 --> 00:03:38.840 align:middle line:84%
Einstein's theory of relativity,
quantum mechanics, particle

00:03:38.840 --> 00:03:41.060 align:middle line:84%
physics all taunt
us with the notion

00:03:41.060 --> 00:03:44.450 align:middle line:84%
that perhaps we can
know the unknowable.

00:03:44.450 --> 00:03:46.370 align:middle line:84%
Yet, these studies
have only begun

00:03:46.370 --> 00:03:48.980 align:middle line:84%
to reveal the intricate
interweaving of forces

00:03:48.980 --> 00:03:50.990 align:middle line:90%
that make up the universe.

00:03:50.990 --> 00:03:54.800 align:middle line:84%
Is it possible these lofty
scientific pursuits are being

00:03:54.800 --> 00:03:58.700 align:middle line:84%
advanced exponentially by
the information contained

00:03:58.700 --> 00:04:03.080 align:middle line:84%
in one ancient, Earthly,
hand-woven piece of cloth?

00:04:03.080 --> 00:04:05.930 align:middle line:90%
Some scientists say yes.

00:04:05.930 --> 00:04:08.840 align:middle line:84%
But in order to understand
how that could be,

00:04:08.840 --> 00:04:11.510 align:middle line:84%
we must first understand the
secrets these scientists are

00:04:11.510 --> 00:04:13.540 align:middle line:90%
trying to uncover.

00:04:13.540 --> 00:04:17.089 align:middle line:84%
>> The basic ideas behind
quantum physics and relativity

00:04:17.089 --> 00:04:19.050 align:middle line:90%
are really quite simple.

00:04:19.050 --> 00:04:23.780 align:middle line:84%
The laws of physics are the same
for all observers regardless

00:04:23.780 --> 00:04:26.330 align:middle line:84%
of where they are and
how fast they're going.

00:04:26.330 --> 00:04:33.290 align:middle line:10%
>> The universe that this model
leads us to is an intelligent,

00:04:33.290 --> 00:04:38.630 align:middle line:10%
self-organizing, creative,
learning, trial and error,

00:04:38.630 --> 00:04:43.280 align:middle line:10%
participatory, interactive,
non-locally interconnected

00:04:43.280 --> 00:04:45.320 align:middle line:10%
evolutionary system.

00:04:45.320 --> 00:04:48.030 align:middle line:90%
That's what it's all about.

00:04:48.030 --> 00:04:50.750 align:middle line:84%
>> That may seem simple
enough to the scientists.

00:04:50.750 --> 00:04:53.750 align:middle line:84%
But how can an awareness
of these concepts

00:04:53.750 --> 00:04:56.570 align:middle line:84%
help us understand the
meaning of why we're here

00:04:56.570 --> 00:04:58.100 align:middle line:90%
and where we're going?

00:04:58.100 --> 00:04:59.720 align:middle line:10%
Is there some
deeper understanding

00:04:59.720 --> 00:05:03.420 align:middle line:10%
that can be gained through
all of this scientific study?

00:05:03.420 --> 00:05:07.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Why do we care about quantum
physics and relativity so much?

00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:10.490 align:middle line:84%
Well, basically they're really
very beautiful theories.

00:05:10.490 --> 00:05:13.640 align:middle line:84%
But if that's all they were, we
wouldn't care very much at all.

00:05:13.640 --> 00:05:15.920 align:middle line:84%
What we feel, though, is
that they're gateways.

00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:20.240 align:middle line:84%
They're leading us into new ways
of understanding the universe.

00:05:20.240 --> 00:05:23.170 align:middle line:84%
And that we care
about very much.

00:05:23.170 --> 00:05:27.590 align:middle line:10%
>> I sincerely think that
through these studies,

00:05:27.590 --> 00:05:33.170 align:middle line:10%
we will come upon a completely
new structure of physics,

00:05:33.170 --> 00:05:38.360 align:middle line:10%
maybe even a completely
different world.

00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:41.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Science has discovered the
basic structure of the entire

00:05:41.270 --> 00:05:45.660 align:middle line:84%
universe by studying the
tiniest possible things.

00:05:45.660 --> 00:05:48.710 align:middle line:10%
And they did it with the largest
scientific instruments ever

00:05:48.710 --> 00:05:54.260 align:middle line:10%
built. One such instrument is
16 miles long, fills a mountain,

00:05:54.260 --> 00:05:57.590 align:middle line:10%
and searches for particles
a trillion times smaller

00:05:57.590 --> 00:05:59.330 align:middle line:10%
than a human hair.

00:05:59.330 --> 00:06:00.770 align:middle line:90%
But why?

00:06:00.770 --> 00:06:04.580 align:middle line:84%
Why search for the
tiniest of tiny particles?

00:06:04.580 --> 00:06:07.500 align:middle line:84%
>> It's been known for a long
time that all physical matter

00:06:07.500 --> 00:06:11.530 align:middle line:84%
emits and reabsorbs
particles of energy.

00:06:11.530 --> 00:06:16.120 align:middle line:84%
Over 100 years ago, Max Planck
named these emissions quanta

00:06:16.120 --> 00:06:18.610 align:middle line:90%
or quantum singularly.

00:06:18.610 --> 00:06:21.940 align:middle line:84%
And they have been the
study of particle physics

00:06:21.940 --> 00:06:23.785 align:middle line:90%
for over 100 years.

00:06:23.785 --> 00:06:26.140 align:middle line:84%
And if you analyze
all the emissions

00:06:26.140 --> 00:06:30.160 align:middle line:84%
from any physical object, that's
called a quantum hologram.

00:06:30.160 --> 00:06:33.760 align:middle line:84%
We now understand that all
physical objects have a quantum

00:06:33.760 --> 00:06:35.920 align:middle line:90%
hologram.

00:06:35.920 --> 00:06:39.850 align:middle line:84%
>> That study has produced a
set of laws that scientists call

00:06:39.850 --> 00:06:41.980 align:middle line:90%
the standard model.

00:06:41.980 --> 00:06:43.960 align:middle line:84%
This is the theory
that summarizes

00:06:43.960 --> 00:06:46.210 align:middle line:84%
the scientists'
current understanding

00:06:46.210 --> 00:06:51.140 align:middle line:84%
of elementary particles and the
fundamental forces of nature.

00:06:51.140 --> 00:06:54.400 align:middle line:84%
>> In fact, what's going on in
the standard model of particle

00:06:54.400 --> 00:06:58.960 align:middle line:84%
physics is extremely mind
bending and paradoxical.

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:02.380 align:middle line:84%
For example, the standard model
says that there are inside

00:07:02.380 --> 00:07:05.260 align:middle line:84%
of the nucleus invisible
particles-- particles we never

00:07:05.260 --> 00:07:07.420 align:middle line:90%
see on their own called quarks.

00:07:07.420 --> 00:07:10.060 align:middle line:84%
And no one has ever
seen a single quark.

00:07:10.060 --> 00:07:12.970 align:middle line:84%
In spite of the fact that
we've achieved a lot of success

00:07:12.970 --> 00:07:15.190 align:middle line:84%
in physics, there's
still a lot of mystery

00:07:15.190 --> 00:07:18.170 align:middle line:90%
here yet to be discovered.

00:07:18.170 --> 00:07:20.320 align:middle line:84%
>> But assuming all
of this is true,

00:07:20.320 --> 00:07:23.215 align:middle line:84%
where can we begin to look for
a meaningful example of what all

00:07:23.215 --> 00:07:25.630 align:middle line:90%
of this means to you and me?

00:07:25.630 --> 00:07:28.810 align:middle line:84%
Is it all just some cosmic
Rubik's cube for scientists

00:07:28.810 --> 00:07:30.280 align:middle line:90%
to play with?

00:07:30.280 --> 00:07:33.190 align:middle line:84%
Or is it possible there
is a broader purpose--

00:07:33.190 --> 00:07:35.380 align:middle line:84%
ancient information
perhaps-- that

00:07:35.380 --> 00:07:38.790 align:middle line:90%
is even more relevant today.

00:07:38.790 --> 00:07:43.260 align:middle line:84%
In the late 1970s, scientists
developed a computer program

00:07:43.260 --> 00:07:46.410 align:middle line:84%
that allowed NASA technicians
to read the terrain

00:07:46.410 --> 00:07:49.530 align:middle line:84%
characteristics of
distant planets derived

00:07:49.530 --> 00:07:52.480 align:middle line:84%
from two-dimensional
satellite photographs.

00:07:52.480 --> 00:07:55.170 align:middle line:84%
But the developers of
this amazing device

00:07:55.170 --> 00:07:57.000 align:middle line:84%
were in for a shock
when they were

00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:00.420 align:middle line:84%
asked to analyze a photograph
of something most of them

00:08:00.420 --> 00:08:02.490 align:middle line:90%
had never even heard of.

00:08:02.490 --> 00:08:04.890 align:middle line:84%
Actually what they
were looking at

00:08:04.890 --> 00:08:09.300 align:middle line:84%
was a two-dimensional photograph
of a two-dimensional artifact.

00:08:09.300 --> 00:08:11.880 align:middle line:84%
But to everyone's
amazement, from somewhere

00:08:11.880 --> 00:08:15.090 align:middle line:84%
there emerged
three-dimensional information.

00:08:15.090 --> 00:08:17.070 align:middle line:84%
To these practical
scientists, it

00:08:17.070 --> 00:08:20.970 align:middle line:84%
was as if they were looking at
something from another planet.

00:08:20.970 --> 00:08:25.260 align:middle line:84%
None of them had ever seen
anything like this before.

00:08:25.260 --> 00:08:29.010 align:middle line:84%
A photograph of an ancient cloth
had brought the scientists face

00:08:29.010 --> 00:08:31.140 align:middle line:90%
to face with the impossible.

00:08:31.140 --> 00:08:34.740 align:middle line:84%
Three--dimensional information
was being discovered where it

00:08:34.740 --> 00:08:37.049 align:middle line:90%
couldn't possibly exist.

00:08:37.049 --> 00:08:39.990 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly, a broad
range of scientists

00:08:39.990 --> 00:08:41.640 align:middle line:84%
took a professional
interest in what

00:08:41.640 --> 00:08:45.180 align:middle line:84%
had been for those who were
even aware of it nothing more

00:08:45.180 --> 00:08:47.250 align:middle line:90%
than a mild curiosity.

00:08:47.250 --> 00:08:50.010 align:middle line:84%
But for one particle
physicist, this tiny fiber

00:08:50.010 --> 00:08:52.470 align:middle line:90%
generated the most excitement.

00:08:52.470 --> 00:08:55.520 align:middle line:84%
It is a single thread
from that same cloth.

00:08:55.520 --> 00:08:58.080 align:middle line:84%
And resting on its
surface is the hint

00:08:58.080 --> 00:09:01.020 align:middle line:84%
of an image that
is barely visible.

00:09:01.020 --> 00:09:05.100 align:middle line:84%
Could it be that somewhere
in the origins of this image

00:09:05.100 --> 00:09:09.640 align:middle line:90%
lay the secrets of the universe?

00:09:09.640 --> 00:09:11.980 align:middle line:84%
The artifact was
the Shroud of Turin.

00:09:11.980 --> 00:09:15.790 align:middle line:84%
And without a doubt, it is
the most picked at, X-rayed,

00:09:15.790 --> 00:09:19.540 align:middle line:84%
examined, revered, reviled,
tested, studied, scanned,

00:09:19.540 --> 00:09:21.845 align:middle line:84%
and photographed artifact
in the world today.

00:09:21.845 --> 00:09:23.310 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09:23.310 --> 00:09:25.740 align:middle line:10%
For those who are unfamiliar
with this particular piece

00:09:25.740 --> 00:09:28.410 align:middle line:10%
of cloth, it has
long been revered

00:09:28.410 --> 00:09:30.840 align:middle line:10%
as the object
described in the Gospel

00:09:30.840 --> 00:09:35.160 align:middle line:10%
according to John Chapter
20 verses 6 and 7.

00:09:35.160 --> 00:09:37.950 align:middle line:10%
Referring to Peter,
John wrote, "He

00:09:37.950 --> 00:09:40.020 align:middle line:10%
saw the strips of
linen lying there,

00:09:40.020 --> 00:09:43.500 align:middle line:10%
as well as the burial cloth that
had been around Jesus' head.

00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:45.700 align:middle line:10%
The cloth was
folded up by itself,

00:09:45.700 --> 00:09:48.300 align:middle line:10%
separate from the linen."

00:09:48.300 --> 00:09:51.600 align:middle line:84%
For over 100 years,
researchers, historians,

00:09:51.600 --> 00:09:53.910 align:middle line:84%
and scientists of
every variety have

00:09:53.910 --> 00:09:57.510 align:middle line:84%
attempted to determine if
this linen cloth tucked away

00:09:57.510 --> 00:10:00.510 align:middle line:84%
in a cathedral in Turin,
Italy could actually

00:10:00.510 --> 00:10:02.430 align:middle line:90%
be the one referred to--

00:10:02.430 --> 00:10:06.040 align:middle line:84%
the burial shroud
of Jesus Christ.

00:10:06.040 --> 00:10:08.110 align:middle line:84%
An attempt was made
to discover the answer

00:10:08.110 --> 00:10:12.430 align:middle line:84%
to that question in 1978 when
a group of American scientists

00:10:12.430 --> 00:10:15.760 align:middle line:84%
were given unprecedented
access to the shroud for 5

00:10:15.760 --> 00:10:18.010 align:middle line:90%
intensive days.

00:10:18.010 --> 00:10:21.100 align:middle line:84%
Over the next several
years, this tireless group

00:10:21.100 --> 00:10:23.950 align:middle line:84%
known as the Shroud of
Turin Research Project,

00:10:23.950 --> 00:10:27.010 align:middle line:84%
or STRP for short,
which was comprised

00:10:27.010 --> 00:10:29.260 align:middle line:84%
of many of the world's
premier scientists

00:10:29.260 --> 00:10:32.300 align:middle line:84%
representing such diverse
disciplines as physics,

00:10:32.300 --> 00:10:36.190 align:middle line:84%
chemistry, engineering, forensic
medicine, and many others

00:10:36.190 --> 00:10:39.970 align:middle line:84%
spent no less than
150,000 man hours

00:10:39.970 --> 00:10:43.630 align:middle line:84%
studying, testing, and
interpreting the data.

00:10:43.630 --> 00:10:46.750 align:middle line:84%
The results seemed to
indicate the shroud could

00:10:46.750 --> 00:10:50.950 align:middle line:84%
be a genuine first century
burial cloth from somewhere

00:10:50.950 --> 00:10:52.600 align:middle line:90%
in Palestine.

00:10:52.600 --> 00:10:55.990 align:middle line:84%
But then in 1988,
carbon dating analysis

00:10:55.990 --> 00:10:58.390 align:middle line:84%
by three different
testing laboratories

00:10:58.390 --> 00:11:00.770 align:middle line:84%
produced quite a
different result.

00:11:00.770 --> 00:11:03.490 align:middle line:84%
>> The radiocarbon dates
that we obtained clearly put

00:11:03.490 --> 00:11:06.250 align:middle line:84%
the shroud, uh, in
the Middle Ages.

00:11:06.250 --> 00:11:08.920 align:middle line:10%
>> According to the
carbon-14 tests,

00:11:08.920 --> 00:11:12.490 align:middle line:10%
the shroud came into existence
somewhere between the years

00:11:12.490 --> 00:11:15.370 align:middle line:10%
1260 and 1390.

00:11:15.370 --> 00:11:18.470 align:middle line:10%
Could all the other
scientists be wrong?

00:11:18.470 --> 00:11:20.980 align:middle line:10%
First of all, we must
point out that the dating

00:11:20.980 --> 00:11:25.270 align:middle line:10%
of a shroud sample in 1988
was both controversial

00:11:25.270 --> 00:11:29.170 align:middle line:10%
and hotly disputed by
experts in many fields.

00:11:29.170 --> 00:11:33.140 align:middle line:10%
>> The problem of
dating a cloth--

00:11:33.140 --> 00:11:37.120 align:middle line:10%
not only the shroud, but I
think any cloth, any old cloth--

00:11:37.120 --> 00:11:42.280 align:middle line:10%
is not easy to solve
completely and definitely.

00:11:42.280 --> 00:11:46.150 align:middle line:84%
>> According to the professor,
the idea of a medieval origin

00:11:46.150 --> 00:11:49.660 align:middle line:84%
of the shroud leads to
an impossible thesis--

00:11:49.660 --> 00:11:52.560 align:middle line:84%
the forger would have had
to find a man to crucify,

00:11:52.560 --> 00:11:55.660 align:middle line:84%
flog him mercilessly,
place him in a shroud,

00:11:55.660 --> 00:11:58.750 align:middle line:84%
and then manufacture or
simply wait for the image

00:11:58.750 --> 00:12:00.940 align:middle line:90%
to somehow appear.

00:12:00.940 --> 00:12:05.020 align:middle line:10%
>> I think that is quite
impossible that what we cannot

00:12:05.020 --> 00:12:06.710 align:middle line:10%
do today--

00:12:06.710 --> 00:12:11.740 align:middle line:10%
it was very easy and
during a medieval period.

00:12:11.740 --> 00:12:16.330 align:middle line:10%
>> 150,000 man hours and the
work of dozens of scientific

00:12:16.330 --> 00:12:19.930 align:middle line:10%
disciplines were challenged--
actually brushed aside--

00:12:19.930 --> 00:12:22.750 align:middle line:10%
by a single carbon-14 test.

00:12:22.750 --> 00:12:25.780 align:middle line:84%
But the world was left
with the same question.

00:12:25.780 --> 00:12:28.000 align:middle line:90%
What created the image?

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:31.030 align:middle line:84%
And how do all of these
latest scientific advances

00:12:31.030 --> 00:12:33.730 align:middle line:84%
lead us to this
particular artifact?

00:12:33.730 --> 00:12:35.470 align:middle line:84%
What is there about
the image that

00:12:35.470 --> 00:12:37.870 align:middle line:84%
causes scientists to
put their reputations

00:12:37.870 --> 00:12:39.880 align:middle line:90%
and fortunes at risk?

00:12:39.880 --> 00:12:45.760 align:middle line:10%
>> The Resurrection itself
belongs to the spiritual world.

00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:49.970 align:middle line:10%
And I don't think it is the
business of physics to--

00:12:49.970 --> 00:12:51.270 align:middle line:10%
to talk about it.

00:12:51.270 --> 00:12:54.400 align:middle line:10%
However, the shroud
itself and what

00:12:54.400 --> 00:12:58.990 align:middle line:10%
made the image leads us to
a mysterious gate, which

00:12:58.990 --> 00:13:00.540 align:middle line:10%
opens for us.

00:13:00.540 --> 00:13:04.870 align:middle line:10%
And it lets us to see a
completely different world,

00:13:04.870 --> 00:13:11.400 align:middle line:10%
an extraordinary world
with extraordinary laws.

00:13:11.400 --> 00:13:12.840 align:middle line:90%
>> What are those laws?

00:13:12.840 --> 00:13:16.230 align:middle line:84%
And do they exist regardless
of the age of the fabric?

00:13:16.230 --> 00:13:18.540 align:middle line:84%
Is this purely a
scientific squabble?

00:13:18.540 --> 00:13:20.280 align:middle line:10%
Or could it be there
is something here

00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:24.090 align:middle line:10%
that is far more important
than the artifact itself?

00:13:24.090 --> 00:13:27.330 align:middle line:10%
Is it possible that the energy
and information now being

00:13:27.330 --> 00:13:29.850 align:middle line:10%
detected is actually
the information

00:13:29.850 --> 00:13:35.430 align:middle line:10%
we need to help us overcome
the problems we face today?

00:13:35.430 --> 00:13:37.260 align:middle line:84%
Are the secrets
of the universe--

00:13:37.260 --> 00:13:39.390 align:middle line:84%
perhaps of all
creation-- locked up

00:13:39.390 --> 00:13:42.570 align:middle line:84%
in this seemingly ordinary
linen burial cloth?

00:13:42.570 --> 00:13:45.570 align:middle line:84%
Can the image-- now known
to contain three-dimensional

00:13:45.570 --> 00:13:49.980 align:middle line:84%
information-- also be
a quantum hologram?

00:13:49.980 --> 00:13:51.960 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps we should take
a moment and define

00:13:51.960 --> 00:13:54.840 align:middle line:84%
exactly what the
Shroud of Turin is

00:13:54.840 --> 00:13:59.460 align:middle line:84%
and what makes it so special
in the minds of so many people.

00:13:59.460 --> 00:14:02.430 align:middle line:84%
The shroud is an ordinary
piece of hand-woven fabric that

00:14:02.430 --> 00:14:08.020 align:middle line:84%
measures 14 feet 3 inches
long and 3 feet 7 inches wide.

00:14:08.020 --> 00:14:11.220 align:middle line:84%
These full-length dark lines
are scorches from the fire that

00:14:11.220 --> 00:14:14.420 align:middle line:90%
nearly destroyed it in 1532.

00:14:14.420 --> 00:14:19.110 align:middle line:84%
The diamond-shaped patches cover
holes resulting from that fire.

00:14:19.110 --> 00:14:21.120 align:middle line:10%
But it is the
faint, ghostly image

00:14:21.120 --> 00:14:23.990 align:middle line:10%
of a crucified man on the
surface of the cloth that

00:14:23.990 --> 00:14:27.390 align:middle line:10%
rivets our attention and
makes this piece of cloth

00:14:27.390 --> 00:14:28.920 align:middle line:10%
unique in all the world.

00:14:28.920 --> 00:14:31.500 align:middle line:90%


00:14:31.500 --> 00:14:34.200 align:middle line:84%
What is the truth
about the Shroud?

00:14:34.200 --> 00:14:36.690 align:middle line:84%
Is it a communication
from another time,

00:14:36.690 --> 00:14:38.340 align:middle line:90%
another dimension?

00:14:38.340 --> 00:14:43.020 align:middle line:84%
And if so, can we determine what
the message is intended to be?

00:14:43.020 --> 00:14:46.100 align:middle line:84%
Could it be that the quantum
revolution in physics

00:14:46.100 --> 00:14:50.760 align:middle line:84%
permits science to go
beyond human speculation?

00:14:50.760 --> 00:14:53.370 align:middle line:84%
According to some
physicists, the world

00:14:53.370 --> 00:14:56.820 align:middle line:84%
is even more extraordinary
than we thought.

00:14:56.820 --> 00:14:58.650 align:middle line:84%
Oddly enough, this
ordinary piece

00:14:58.650 --> 00:15:01.230 align:middle line:84%
of linen cloth that
many scientists believe

00:15:01.230 --> 00:15:04.200 align:middle line:84%
to be over 2,000 years
old might give scientists

00:15:04.200 --> 00:15:07.020 align:middle line:84%
their most tangible clue
to unlocking the secrets

00:15:07.020 --> 00:15:09.360 align:middle line:90%
of the quantum hologram.

00:15:09.360 --> 00:15:12.960 align:middle line:84%
Yet, some still maintain
the carbon-14 test

00:15:12.960 --> 00:15:16.620 align:middle line:84%
places its scientific value
under a cloud of suspicion.

00:15:16.620 --> 00:15:18.870 align:middle line:10%
>> There are hundreds
of pieces of evidence,

00:15:18.870 --> 00:15:23.130 align:middle line:10%
both scientific and historical,
that indicate that the Shroud

00:15:23.130 --> 00:15:24.760 align:middle line:10%
is authentic.

00:15:24.760 --> 00:15:26.310 align:middle line:10%
There is only one
piece of evidence

00:15:26.310 --> 00:15:29.400 align:middle line:10%
that says the shroud
is not authentic.

00:15:29.400 --> 00:15:30.780 align:middle line:10%
And that's carbon-14.

00:15:30.780 --> 00:15:36.660 align:middle line:10%
However, carbon-14 has
itself been much disputed.

00:15:36.660 --> 00:15:39.930 align:middle line:10%
It is neither logical,
empirical, or scientific

00:15:39.930 --> 00:15:42.960 align:middle line:10%
to take one piece of
evidence and ignore

00:15:42.960 --> 00:15:44.790 align:middle line:10%
the hundreds of
pieces of evidence

00:15:44.790 --> 00:15:48.090 align:middle line:10%
in support of authenticity.

00:15:48.090 --> 00:15:50.430 align:middle line:84%
>> We are faced
with a paradox here.

00:15:50.430 --> 00:15:52.530 align:middle line:84%
All of the scientific
analysis seems

00:15:52.530 --> 00:15:56.010 align:middle line:84%
to place the cloth in
Jerusalem in the first century.

00:15:56.010 --> 00:16:00.300 align:middle line:84%
But the carbon-14 test makes
the shroud unequivocally a 13th

00:16:00.300 --> 00:16:02.310 align:middle line:90%
century relic.

00:16:02.310 --> 00:16:06.090 align:middle line:84%
What if both
analyses are correct?

00:16:06.090 --> 00:16:08.400 align:middle line:84%
But how could the
carbon-14 tests

00:16:08.400 --> 00:16:10.650 align:middle line:84%
be as accurate as
modern technology can

00:16:10.650 --> 00:16:14.610 align:middle line:84%
make them and all of the
other scientific data that

00:16:14.610 --> 00:16:19.200 align:middle line:84%
places the cloth solidly in the
first century also be accurate?

00:16:19.200 --> 00:16:23.550 align:middle line:84%
That possibility was suggested
at the Sindone 2000 Worldwide

00:16:23.550 --> 00:16:26.540 align:middle line:90%
Congress in Orvieto, Italy.

00:16:26.540 --> 00:16:31.320 align:middle line:84%
Authors M Sue Benford and
Joseph Marino posited the notion

00:16:31.320 --> 00:16:34.410 align:middle line:84%
that a 16th century
invisible patch

00:16:34.410 --> 00:16:38.910 align:middle line:84%
had skewed the 1988 carbon-14
test on the sample taken

00:16:38.910 --> 00:16:40.860 align:middle line:90%
from the Shroud of Turin.

00:16:40.860 --> 00:16:43.470 align:middle line:84%
Their idea was backed
by what seemed to be

00:16:43.470 --> 00:16:45.630 align:middle line:90%
solid historical research.

00:16:45.630 --> 00:16:47.700 align:middle line:84%
But the whole notion
was immediately

00:16:47.700 --> 00:16:50.820 align:middle line:84%
rejected as being
technically impossible.

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:53.760 align:middle line:84%
At this point another scientist,
one of the original STRP team,

00:16:53.760 --> 00:16:55.020 align:middle line:90%
became interested.

00:16:55.020 --> 00:16:57.510 align:middle line:10%
Like others who had closely
examined the shroud,

00:16:57.510 --> 00:17:02.160 align:middle line:10%
he, too, was very skeptical of
the whole idea of reweaving.

00:17:02.160 --> 00:17:04.109 align:middle line:84%
The late Raymond
Rogers set himself

00:17:04.109 --> 00:17:06.450 align:middle line:84%
the task of discovering
whether or not

00:17:06.450 --> 00:17:09.150 align:middle line:84%
scientific analysis could
resolve the issue once

00:17:09.150 --> 00:17:10.619 align:middle line:90%
and for all.

00:17:10.619 --> 00:17:12.660 align:middle line:84%
Rogers obtained
samples of the Shroud

00:17:12.660 --> 00:17:16.780 align:middle line:84%
immediately adjacent to the
area used in the carbon-14 test.

00:17:16.780 --> 00:17:19.230 align:middle line:10%
These were provided by
Gilbert Raes, the man who

00:17:19.230 --> 00:17:20.790 align:middle line:10%
had originally removed them.

00:17:20.790 --> 00:17:23.670 align:middle line:10%
In an interview unveiled
at the 2005 Dallas

00:17:23.670 --> 00:17:27.150 align:middle line:10%
Symposium on the Shroud,
Rogers told the interviewer--

00:17:27.150 --> 00:17:29.910 align:middle line:10%
>> This is just
about the last straw.

00:17:29.910 --> 00:17:34.200 align:middle line:84%
I've got the samples that
can shoot that full of holes.

00:17:34.200 --> 00:17:36.270 align:middle line:90%
So I got out the Raes samples.

00:17:36.270 --> 00:17:39.270 align:middle line:84%
And I got out some of
the shroud samples.

00:17:39.270 --> 00:17:41.130 align:middle line:90%
And I went to work again.

00:17:41.130 --> 00:17:43.770 align:middle line:84%
And lo and behold in
less than an hour,

00:17:43.770 --> 00:17:46.890 align:middle line:84%
I knew that the Raes
sample was totally

00:17:46.890 --> 00:17:49.520 align:middle line:84%
different in
chemical composition

00:17:49.520 --> 00:17:52.350 align:middle line:84%
than the main part
of the shroud.

00:17:52.350 --> 00:17:57.480 align:middle line:84%
And then the shocker
that really shook me up--

00:17:57.480 --> 00:18:00.780 align:middle line:84%
in looking at the
Raes threads, I

00:18:00.780 --> 00:18:04.550 align:middle line:84%
hit this one that was
an end to end splice.

00:18:04.550 --> 00:18:06.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's exactly
the sort of thing

00:18:06.900 --> 00:18:09.270 align:middle line:84%
that Benford and
Marino were talking

00:18:09.270 --> 00:18:13.050 align:middle line:84%
about in this
invisible reweaving.

00:18:13.050 --> 00:18:15.000 align:middle line:84%
>> After coming to
this conclusion,

00:18:15.000 --> 00:18:18.200 align:middle line:84%
ray called me one day
and said flat out, Tom,

00:18:18.200 --> 00:18:21.200 align:middle line:84%
there is no scientific
wiggle room.

00:18:21.200 --> 00:18:24.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Up to this point, then,
we can say with some degree

00:18:24.140 --> 00:18:27.800 align:middle line:84%
of scientific certainty that
the Shroud is an authentic first

00:18:27.800 --> 00:18:29.610 align:middle line:90%
century fabric.

00:18:29.610 --> 00:18:32.210 align:middle line:84%
Some scientists may
continue to disagree.

00:18:32.210 --> 00:18:36.020 align:middle line:84%
But for the moment at least,
the 1988 carbon-14 tests

00:18:36.020 --> 00:18:39.020 align:middle line:84%
on the Shroud appear to
have been invalidated.

00:18:39.020 --> 00:18:43.040 align:middle line:84%
In the meantime, a group of
digital scientists in Amsterdam

00:18:43.040 --> 00:18:45.590 align:middle line:84%
focused their expertise
on a different set of data

00:18:45.590 --> 00:18:47.060 align:middle line:90%
from the shroud.

00:18:47.060 --> 00:18:50.210 align:middle line:84%
What they found
stunned them all.

00:18:50.210 --> 00:18:54.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Holographic information
is encoded in the shroud

00:18:54.340 --> 00:18:56.030 align:middle line:90%
in an interference pattern.

00:18:56.030 --> 00:18:59.500 align:middle line:84%
And most probably there's
more information in it,

00:18:59.500 --> 00:19:03.440 align:middle line:84%
which I call like a blueprint
of the universe, maybe

00:19:03.440 --> 00:19:05.770 align:middle line:90%
an opening to a new science.

00:19:05.770 --> 00:19:07.760 align:middle line:90%
You come in an unknown land.

00:19:07.760 --> 00:19:08.780 align:middle line:90%
You don't have a GPS.

00:19:08.780 --> 00:19:10.400 align:middle line:90%
You don't have a map.

00:19:10.400 --> 00:19:11.750 align:middle line:90%
It's completely new.

00:19:11.750 --> 00:19:14.678 align:middle line:90%
You have to reinvent science.

00:19:14.678 --> 00:19:16.220 align:middle line:84%
And I think that is
one of the things

00:19:16.220 --> 00:19:19.340 align:middle line:90%
that the Shroud is all about.

00:19:19.340 --> 00:19:22.090 align:middle line:10%
>> But even if we are to accept
the shroud as a genuine first

00:19:22.090 --> 00:19:25.420 align:middle line:10%
century fabric, that's only
one piece of the puzzle.

00:19:25.420 --> 00:19:28.120 align:middle line:84%
Validating the age of
the fabric is important.

00:19:28.120 --> 00:19:29.710 align:middle line:84%
But the work being
done in Holland

00:19:29.710 --> 00:19:33.700 align:middle line:84%
promises even more
exciting revelations.

00:19:33.700 --> 00:19:36.580 align:middle line:84%
If the fabric has been proven
to be a genuine first century

00:19:36.580 --> 00:19:39.250 align:middle line:84%
material, could it be there
is supporting evidence

00:19:39.250 --> 00:19:42.400 align:middle line:84%
to suggest this very
fabric might, in fact, be

00:19:42.400 --> 00:19:45.490 align:middle line:84%
the actual burial
shroud of Jesus Christ?

00:19:45.490 --> 00:19:48.160 align:middle line:84%
Have these scientists discovered
something in the image

00:19:48.160 --> 00:19:54.000 align:middle line:84%
itself that places this piece of
cloth in a tomb near Golgotha,

00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:57.990 align:middle line:84%
which brings us to the next and
so far unanswered question--

00:19:57.990 --> 00:19:59.710 align:middle line:90%
how did the image get there?

00:19:59.710 --> 00:20:02.970 align:middle line:90%


00:20:02.970 --> 00:20:05.010 align:middle line:10%
There can be no doubt
that the Shroud of Turin

00:20:05.010 --> 00:20:07.290 align:middle line:10%
has been venerated
for hundreds of years

00:20:07.290 --> 00:20:09.840 align:middle line:10%
by the faithful as the
cloth or sheet that

00:20:09.840 --> 00:20:12.690 align:middle line:10%
covered the body of
the crucified Christ.

00:20:12.690 --> 00:20:15.390 align:middle line:84%
Nor can there be any doubt
that the Shroud exists.

00:20:15.390 --> 00:20:18.390 align:middle line:84%
It has been touched, handled,
photographed, and examined

00:20:18.390 --> 00:20:20.190 align:middle line:90%
in every way imaginable.

00:20:20.190 --> 00:20:23.910 align:middle line:84%
But has the result of all the
research, testing, and study

00:20:23.910 --> 00:20:28.090 align:middle line:84%
brought us any closer to proving
not only the age of the fabric,

00:20:28.090 --> 00:20:30.710 align:middle line:84%
but the reason for
its veneration?

00:20:30.710 --> 00:20:33.420 align:middle line:84%
There are those who insist
the authenticity of the shroud

00:20:33.420 --> 00:20:35.010 align:middle line:90%
has not been proven.

00:20:35.010 --> 00:20:36.960 align:middle line:84%
What's more, they
contend the idea

00:20:36.960 --> 00:20:39.000 align:middle line:84%
that it once wrapped
the crucified body

00:20:39.000 --> 00:20:44.190 align:middle line:84%
of the historic Jesus can
indeed never be proven.

00:20:44.190 --> 00:20:46.890 align:middle line:84%
Recently others have
challenged that assumption.

00:20:46.890 --> 00:20:49.500 align:middle line:84%
And the search for historic
and scientific evidence

00:20:49.500 --> 00:20:52.440 align:middle line:84%
that might corroborate the
authenticity of the shroud

00:20:52.440 --> 00:20:53.680 align:middle line:90%
goes on.

00:20:53.680 --> 00:20:57.510 align:middle line:84%
And even Cardinal Severino
Poletto, the papal custodian

00:20:57.510 --> 00:20:59.880 align:middle line:84%
of the Holy Shroud at
the cathedral in Turin

00:20:59.880 --> 00:21:02.220 align:middle line:90%
finds the search fascinating.

00:21:02.220 --> 00:21:04.740 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:21:04.740 --> 00:21:07.890 align:middle line:10%
>> My attitude toward science
is one of great respect.

00:21:07.890 --> 00:21:10.650 align:middle line:84%
And scientists, many scientists
in the world, study the shroud

00:21:10.650 --> 00:21:11.790 align:middle line:90%
and carry out research.

00:21:11.790 --> 00:21:13.680 align:middle line:10%
And they see what can
be discovered step

00:21:13.680 --> 00:21:15.250 align:middle line:10%
by step as studies proceed.

00:21:15.250 --> 00:21:19.390 align:middle line:10%
>> [SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

00:21:19.390 --> 00:21:21.840 align:middle line:10%
>> And if science in the
future offers us well-founded

00:21:21.840 --> 00:21:26.570 align:middle line:10%
and incontrovertible elements,
we will always be delighted.

00:21:26.570 --> 00:21:29.970 align:middle line:10%
Pope John Paul II said that it
was not the task of the church,

00:21:29.970 --> 00:21:32.400 align:middle line:10%
but of the historians
and scientists to define

00:21:32.400 --> 00:21:36.510 align:middle line:10%
whether it is authentic or not.

00:21:36.510 --> 00:21:38.790 align:middle line:10%
>> For a significant
number of researchers,

00:21:38.790 --> 00:21:42.000 align:middle line:10%
at least some answers could very
well be found in a cathedral

00:21:42.000 --> 00:21:44.140 align:middle line:10%
in Oviedo, Spain.

00:21:44.140 --> 00:21:47.850 align:middle line:84%
>> In chapter 20 of
the fourth Gospel,

00:21:47.850 --> 00:21:50.760 align:middle line:90%
we read how the two disciples--

00:21:50.760 --> 00:21:54.120 align:middle line:84%
the beloved disciple and Peter--
ran to the tomb on Easter

00:21:54.120 --> 00:21:56.790 align:middle line:84%
morning having heard
that the tomb was empty.

00:21:56.790 --> 00:22:00.210 align:middle line:84%
Now there's been all
kinds of speculation

00:22:00.210 --> 00:22:02.130 align:middle line:84%
as to the position
of the cloths--

00:22:02.130 --> 00:22:03.420 align:middle line:90%
how they saw them.

00:22:03.420 --> 00:22:05.130 align:middle line:90%
But really that's unnecessary.

00:22:05.130 --> 00:22:08.730 align:middle line:84%
The original Greek text is
really quite clear on that.

00:22:08.730 --> 00:22:11.890 align:middle line:84%
>> And the other disciple
ran more quickly than Peter

00:22:11.890 --> 00:22:13.880 align:middle line:84%
and came first to the
tomb and stooping,

00:22:13.880 --> 00:22:15.750 align:middle line:90%
sees lying the sheets.

00:22:15.750 --> 00:22:18.750 align:middle line:84%
Comes, therefore, also
Simon, Peter following him,

