00:33:33.360 --> 00:33:36.160 align:middle line:90%
in 29 AD to 33.

00:33:36.160 --> 00:33:38.440 align:middle line:84%
We can identify
the images of them.

00:33:38.440 --> 00:33:41.580 align:middle line:10%
And so we can identify
the particular coin

00:33:41.580 --> 00:33:44.290 align:middle line:10%
and know the origin as
well as the date, which

00:33:44.290 --> 00:33:48.300 align:middle line:10%
for both of them that we
identify were struck in 29 AD.

00:33:48.300 --> 00:33:52.330 align:middle line:84%
So this dates the shroud
back to the first century.

00:33:52.330 --> 00:33:55.740 align:middle line:84%
It also localizes that to Israel
since that these coins are just

00:33:55.740 --> 00:33:57.943 align:middle line:84%
the widow's might or the
common penny of the time,

00:33:57.943 --> 00:33:59.610 align:middle line:84%
and certainly would
not circulate either

00:33:59.610 --> 00:34:02.790 align:middle line:84%
outside of Israel or not
very long after the reign

00:34:02.790 --> 00:34:05.940 align:middle line:84%
of Tiberius Caesar to
which they were dedicated.

00:34:05.940 --> 00:34:08.489 align:middle line:84%
>> But how could an image
containing so much information

00:34:08.489 --> 00:34:09.810 align:middle line:90%
have been formed?

00:34:09.810 --> 00:34:11.940 align:middle line:84%
There are those who believe
the image could only

00:34:11.940 --> 00:34:15.389 align:middle line:84%
have been formed by a burst
