00:34:15.389 --> 00:34:19.440 align:middle line:84%
But the simple fact is nothing
like the shroud image has ever

00:34:19.440 --> 00:34:21.870 align:middle line:90%
been found or reproduced.

00:34:21.870 --> 00:34:24.600 align:middle line:84%
But that's only the beginning
of the astounding information

00:34:24.600 --> 00:34:27.030 align:middle line:84%
to be gleaned from
this amazing image.

00:34:27.030 --> 00:34:29.250 align:middle line:84%
In spite of skeptics
and setbacks,

00:34:29.250 --> 00:34:31.679 align:middle line:84%
scientists continue
their search.

00:34:31.679 --> 00:34:34.560 align:middle line:84%
And Dame Isabel Piczek,
a particle physicist,

00:34:34.560 --> 00:34:36.630 align:middle line:84%
believes the shroud
has brought science

00:34:36.630 --> 00:34:40.730 align:middle line:84%
to the threshold of a whole
new understanding of physics.

00:34:40.730 --> 00:34:44.250 align:middle line:84%
While dealing with the position
of the body within the cloth,

00:34:44.250 --> 00:34:47.100 align:middle line:84%
she discovered one of those
mysterious properties that

00:34:47.100 --> 00:34:50.760 align:middle line:90%
cannot be, yet somehow is--

00:34:50.760 --> 00:34:54.870 align:middle line:84%
an interface that divides
the image transport into two

00:34:54.870 --> 00:34:58.830 align:middle line:84%
hermetically separate yet
simultaneous actions and forces

00:34:58.830 --> 00:35:03.810 align:middle line:84%
causing the shroud to be taut
and parallel on both sides,

00:35:03.810 --> 00:35:08.470 align:middle line:90%
creating a true event horizon.

00:35:08.470 --> 00:35:11.400 align:middle line:84%
>> In general relativity,
we have found that there are

00:35:11.400 --> 00:35:14.090 align:middle line:84%
certain things
called black holes.

00:35:14.090 --> 00:35:19.170 align:middle line:10%
Now the surface of a black hole
is called an event horizon.

00:35:19.170 --> 00:35:22.410 align:middle line:84%
And it's called that because
right at that surface--

00:35:22.410 --> 00:35:25.290 align:middle line:84%
right at that surface
the laws of physics

00:35:25.290 --> 00:35:29.820 align:middle line:84%
seem to change
character drastically.

00:35:29.820 --> 00:35:32.130 align:middle line:10%
>> When you look at the
image of the shroud--

00:35:32.130 --> 00:35:34.920 align:middle line:10%
the two bodies next
to each other--

00:35:34.920 --> 00:35:37.690 align:middle line:10%
you feel that it's a flat image.

00:35:37.690 --> 00:35:42.036 align:middle line:10%
But if you create, for instance,
a three-dimensional object as I

00:35:42.036 --> 00:35:43.810 align:middle line:10%
did-- the real body--

00:35:43.810 --> 00:35:46.596 align:middle line:10%
then you realize that there--

00:35:46.596 --> 00:35:50.940 align:middle line:10%
there is a strange
dividing element,

00:35:50.940 --> 00:35:56.850 align:middle line:10%
an interface from which
the image is projected up.

00:35:56.850 --> 00:35:59.590 align:middle line:10%
And the image is projected down.

00:35:59.590 --> 00:36:06.060 align:middle line:10%
The muscles of the body
are absolutely not crossed

00:36:06.060 --> 00:36:10.200 align:middle line:10%
against the stone of the tomb.

00:36:10.200 --> 00:36:11.880 align:middle line:10%
They are perfect.

00:36:11.880 --> 00:36:16.140 align:middle line:10%
It means that the body is
hovering between the two

00:36:16.140 --> 00:36:18.450 align:middle line:10%
sides of the shroud.

00:36:18.450 --> 00:36:19.800 align:middle line:10%
What does that mean?

00:36:19.800 --> 00:36:22.750 align:middle line:10%
That there is
absolutely no gravity.

00:36:22.750 --> 00:36:26.940 align:middle line:10%
Other strange things you
discover-- that the--

00:36:26.940 --> 00:36:30.410 align:middle line:10%
the image is
absolutely undistorted.

00:36:30.410 --> 00:36:33.860 align:middle line:10%
Now if you imagine that
the cloth was wrinkled,

00:36:33.860 --> 00:36:37.950 align:middle line:10%
tied, wrapped around the
body and all of a sudden

00:36:37.950 --> 00:36:41.970 align:middle line:10%
you see a perfect image,
which is impossible

00:36:41.970 --> 00:36:45.480 align:middle line:10%
unless the shroud was
made absolutely taut--

00:36:45.480 --> 00:36:47.060 align:middle line:10%
rigidly taut.

00:36:47.060 --> 00:36:49.700 align:middle line:10%


00:36:49.700 --> 00:36:53.960 align:middle line:10%
Everybody thinks that
the tomb signifies death.

00:36:53.960 --> 00:36:56.970 align:middle line:10%
Not at all-- the exact opposite.

00:36:56.970 --> 00:37:00.140 align:middle line:10%
The shroud and
the tomb signifies

00:37:00.140 --> 00:37:04.730 align:middle line:10%
an unbelievable
beginning, because the--

00:37:04.730 --> 00:37:09.200 align:middle line:10%
in the depth of the
collapsed event horizon,

00:37:09.200 --> 00:37:13.150 align:middle line:10%
there is something which
science knows as singularity--

00:37:13.150 --> 00:37:16.880 align:middle line:10%
that this is exactly
what started the universe

00:37:16.880 --> 00:37:18.320 align:middle line:10%
in the Big Bang.

00:37:18.320 --> 00:37:21.200 align:middle line:10%
We have nothing less
in the tomb of Christ

00:37:21.200 --> 00:37:26.190 align:middle line:10%
than the beginning
of a new universe.

00:37:26.190 --> 00:37:29.250 align:middle line:84%
>> For centuries, the shroud
has been viewed and analyzed

00:37:29.250 --> 00:37:31.110 align:middle line:90%
as a record of a death--

00:37:31.110 --> 00:37:33.480 align:middle line:90%
the end of the physical being.

00:37:33.480 --> 00:37:37.060 align:middle line:84%
