record not of an ending,

00:37:40.620 --> 00:37:43.740 align:middle line:84%
but a beginning, which
would suggest Resurrection

00:37:43.740 --> 00:37:46.150 align:middle line:90%
in its truest sense.

00:37:46.150 --> 00:37:48.150 align:middle line:84%
And according to
Dame Piczek, this

00:37:48.150 --> 00:37:51.210 align:middle line:84%
is the starting base
for the new physics.

00:37:51.210 --> 00:37:53.940 align:middle line:84%
But is Isabel Piczek
out on a limb of physics

00:37:53.940 --> 00:37:56.400 align:middle line:90%
where no one else wants to go?

00:37:56.400 --> 00:37:59.490 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps not-- recently
a group of scientists

00:37:59.490 --> 00:38:01.500 align:middle line:84%
trying to identify
those things that

00:38:01.500 --> 00:38:03.120 align:middle line:84%
are fundamental
to the way nature

00:38:03.120 --> 00:38:06.420 align:middle line:84%
works made some
startling discoveries.

00:38:06.420 --> 00:38:08.490 align:middle line:10%
Dr. Edgar Mitchell--
the sixth man

00:38:08.490 --> 00:38:11.460 align:middle line:10%
to walk on the moon, founder
of the Institute of Noetic

00:38:11.460 --> 00:38:14.940 align:middle line:10%
Sciences, author, and
lecturer explains.

00:38:14.940 --> 00:38:17.550 align:middle line:10%
>> The classical traditional
model in physics,

00:38:17.550 --> 00:38:22.890 align:middle line:10%
which began in Newtonian
times describes how particles

00:38:22.890 --> 00:38:27.930 align:middle line:10%
and atoms and molecules
move and recombine.

00:38:27.930 --> 00:38:30.810 align:middle line:84%
Even most of the 20th
century, physicists

00:38:30.810 --> 00:38:33.450 align:middle line:84%
